race.description: Mclardy Mcshane Insurance Swan Hill Handicap (Bm56)
race.comment: SNAPSHOT (12) impressed when successful as favourite over 900m at Albury on debut 17 days ago. Led them up in that off strong jumpout form. Sure to be further improved and can make it back-to-back wins. BOURBON ROAD (3) resumed from a spell beaten 1.8L at Mildura over 1000m when he worked home strongly. Doesn't have the best strike rate but he is still well shy of his best and Coffey is a positive jockey engagement. A chance with average luck in the run. MISSED THE MARK (4) spiked his numbers at Warrnambool storming home from the back beaten narrowly. He is capable of sitting closer and has to be considered. EPIC CENTRE (1) resumes and has switched from the Clayton Douglas stable. He has the speed to clear the wide barrier and has a handy 3kg claim in easier class. Has the ability and is worth a market watch.
